4. WHY NAIVE FIXES FAIL

Before presenting ZTFM, we demonstrate that obvious mitigations are insufficient:

Naive Fix Why It Fails
TLS for FMAPI Attacker with any valid tenant certificate (common in multi-tenant clusters) can still issue commands
Port-based filtering PCIe Requester ID can be spoofed (no cryptographic protection in CXL.io)
Rate limiting per tenant ATK-4 doesn't require high rate; ATK-5 uses single tenant
Zero DCD extents on release Not required by CXL 3.1 spec (Section 8.2.4); vendor-dependent
Audit logging Detects but does not prevent attacks (reactive only)

Conclusion: A reference monitor with mandatory authentication and ownership invariants is required.

